        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 24 at 5:41PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 541 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Longmont, or 25 miles southwest of Greeley, moving northeast at 25
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree branches and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Longmont, Johnstown, Berthoud, Mead and Platteville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
